    "number": 34933,
    "state": "open",
    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": true,
    "title": "net: cbfilters: Don't disconnect peers for requesting unknown blocks.",
    "user": {
      "login": "davidgumberg",
      "id": 2257631,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIyNTc2MzE=",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2257631?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/davidgumberg",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/davidgumberg/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "Some BIP157 light clients are not complying with the following requirement:\r\n\r\n> StopHash MUST be known to belong to a block accepted by the receiving peer. This is the case if the peer had previously sent a `headers` or `inv` message with that block or any descendents. A node that receives [`getcf(ilter|header|checkpt)s`]with an unknown StopHash SHOULD NOT respond.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0157.mediawiki#getcfilters\r\n\r\nDuring the recent 2-block reorg I observed on one node's logs that it disconnected BIP157 peers with the version string `/btcwire:0.5.0/neutrino:0.12.0-beta/` for asking for filters from the other side of the block race:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[net] peer requested invalid block hash: 95b0d0f836f18d78dfbae435fb37bf6fff2e37a4fc01c20be8495bc3ea4fbb58, disconnecting peer=8502032, [...]\r\n```\r\n\r\n(https://bnoc.xyz/t/raw-data-request-block-filter-peers-being-disconnected-due-to-invalid-block-requests/101)\r\n\r\nThe broken implementations should fix themselves, but disconnecting is too harsh of a punishment for this mistake, this PR keeps the log message and returns early without responding when this happens, but doesn't set `fDisconnect=true`.",
    "labels": [
      {
        "id": 98298007,
        "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw5ODI5ODAwNw==",
